Latex Template System

description
lt makes creating new latex proects and files easier by using your own
templates and placing them in your own project directory suckless style

options
-h  help
-t  type of template
-n  name of project

setup
give the path of your .tex templates folder in config.h, but make sure
that there is a foreward slash (/) at the end of the path

usage
example: lt -t mla -n project
make sure that the type you enter is the same as the name of the template
that you wish to use (without the .tex extension)
